{"type":"message","id":"6a918823","parentId":"44a3c977","timestamp":"2026-05-17T13:37:15.030Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I can see `tiktok_product_detail` does return product data, but for US site it returned an Air Fryer product - not hair clips. The user is right that the product ID is returned by some API calls.\n\nThe issue is: `tiktok_category_report` for VN site only returns titles, prices, etc. without ProductId. The user is pointing out that other API calls like `tiktok_similar_product` do return `ProductId` field.\n\nLet me look at the schema for `tiktok_similar_product` to understand what it returns.Actually, let me just test the full flow now. \n\nI'm realizing the core issue: the VN `tiktok_category_report` endpoint returns product metadata without the ProductId field, so even though the user showed me a successful response with a ProductId of 1731002875688620178, that data came from a different API call (US site variant of `tiktok_product_detail`). To write TikTok links to the Feishu \"附件\" field, I need those ProductIds first. Let me query `tiktok_similar_product` on VN to see if that returns the missing IDs.\n","thinkingSignature":"efa2bfe6cb9370247c2477572eb12be51feefe97f9379a97ea8616647c5ba89b"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n你说得对！`tiktok_product_detail` 返回的数据里有 `ProductId`。只是 VN 类目报告里没带出这个字段。\n\n让我用 `tiktok_similar_product` 搜一下 VN 站的发饰产品，看看能不能拿到带 ProductId 的数据：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_v85ux5fzqhbg_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"mcporter call sorftime-test.tiktok_similar_product keywords:\"hair clip\" site:VN --output json 2>/dev/null | python3 -c \"\nimport json,sys\ndata = json.load(sys.stdin)\nprint(type(data), len(data) if isinstance(data,list) else 'not list')\nprint(json.dumps(data, ensure_ascii=False, indent=2)[:3000])\n\" 2>/dev/null"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":988,"output":407,"cacheRead":51520,"cacheWri