{"type":"message","id":"f3114bc4","parentId":"912eb275","timestamp":"2026-05-17T14:23:13.099Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is asking whether I'm a script or a cron job. They're asking about how the daily selection task will run.\n\nI need to clarify - I'm an AI agent (OpenClaw agent), not a pure script or cron. The \"scheduled task\" concept comes from the SOP's work rhythm section, but there's no actual cron configured yet. The user seems to be asking how the 9am daily selection will actually run.\n\nLooking at the OpenClaw docs, I can use `update_plan` or a cron-like mechanism. Let me check if there's a way to set up scheduled tasks in OpenClaw. Actually, looking at the heartbeat section in AGENTS.md, it mentions cron can be used for precise timing. But I don't think we've actually set up a cron task yet.\n\nThe user seems to be questioning whether the automated execution is actually set up, or whether I was just saying \"tomorrow at 9am\" as a concept.\n\nI should be honest - I haven't actually set up a cron job yet. The 9am timing was a plan we discussed but not yet configured. I should clarify what the actual setup looks like.\n\nI should use update_plan to track the plan, and potentially set up a cron if needed. But first let me explain the current state - I'm an AI agent, not a script/cron. For automated daily execution, we'd need to either:\n1. Set up a cron job (if OpenClaw supports it)\n2. Use a sub-agent to handle the daily execution\n3. The user manually triggers when they want to run\n\nLet me be honest and explain the situation.\n","thinkingSignature":"57e00aa751ce2a9495df11f1d51b21f9b00db90ae593cdbf5c30dd187446c2ba"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_z0vj2a95xoth_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"ls /home/halei/workspace-tts/config/ | grep -i cron"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":271,"output":371,"cacheRead":115520,"cacheWrite":0