{"type":"custom_message","customType":"openclaw.runtime-context","content":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"chat_id\": \"user:ou_42b0f5aa88c1415647c200a3dc0a8f68\",\n  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b6fa8b5a888acb2137ddb96741a2\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"ou_42b0f5aa88c1415647c200a3dc0a8f68\",\n  \"sender\": \"ou_42b0f5aa88c1415647c200a3dc0a8f68\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Sun 2026-05-17 22:24 GMT+8\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"ou_42b0f5aa88c1415647c200a3dc0a8f68\",\n  \"id\": \"ou_42b0f5aa88c1415647c200a3dc0a8f68\",\n  \"name\": \"ou_42b0f5aa88c1415647c200a3dc0a8f68\"\n}\n```","display":false,"details":{"source":"openclaw-runtime-context"},"id":"e68e5fb7","parentId":"f70ee924","timestamp":"2026-05-17T14:24:58.136Z"}
{"type":"message","id":"4f4e774d","parentId":"e68e5fb7","timestamp":"2026-05-17T14:25:47.338Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is asking me to decide which approach is better. Let me think about this:\n\n**Cron approach:**\n- Runs at exact scheduled time (e.g., 9:00 AM every day)\n- Independent session, doesn't require the agent to be \"alive\"\n- More precise timing\n- But: needs to store state about last run, needs to write results somewhere\n\n**Heartbeat approach:**\n- Uses the existing HEARTBEAT.md mechanism\n- Agent is periodically woken up to do checks\n- Can batch with other checks (email, calendar, etc.)\n- Less precise timing (around a time window)\n- Uses existing infrastructure\n\nFor this use case (daily product selection at 9am), cron is more appropriate because:\n1. We need exact timing (9am every day)\n2. It's a focused task - run selection, write to Feishu, done\n3. We don't need the agent to be \"always on\" between runs\n\nHowever, I should note that OpenClaw's cron system is not something I've configured yet. Let me think about how to set it up.\n\nActually, looking at the docs and workspace, I need to set up a cron job that triggers the TTS agent. But I'm not sure if OpenClaw has a built-in cron or if I need to use system cron.\n\nActually, looking back at the system prompts and tools - there's no explicit cron tool in my toolkit. The \"heartbeat\" mechanism in HEARTBEAT.md is more about periodic checks when the agent is active, not a scheduled trigger.\n\nFor a daily scheduled task, the most straightforward approach would be:\n1. Use system cron with `openclaw` CLI\n2. Or set up a scheduled task via the OpenClaw agent system\n\nBut since I don't have a specific \"cron\" tool, let me think about what's actually possible...\n\nActually, I can write a script that runs the selection process and use system cron to schedule it. \n\nThe cleanest solution is a cron job that triggers a separate OpenClaw session to run the selection task, then completes. This way I can set it up and let it run automatically without needing to manually trigger anything each day.\n","thinkingSignature":"f7d0858e99fcbf1edc5101eeeb6bb3e2485b95a67830f56f77df6bb53505bbcf"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n建议用 **Cron**，原因：\n\n1. **精准定时** → 每天 9:00 稳定跑，不依赖我是否在线\n2. **独立 session** → 跑完就结束，不占用资源\n3. **专注一件事** → 选品 → 写入 → 结束，流程干净\n\n我现在帮你配一个 cron job：\n\n```bash\n0 9 * * * openclaw sessions spawn --agent tts --task \"执行今日选品：跑Sorftime VN类目报告，筛选Top10（增长率>0+评分≥100+毛利率≥30%），写入飞书表格AKppbAeyXanToTsVl6ScxO5QnZd，发送飞书通知\" --runtime subagent\n```\n\n每天 9:00 触发一个新 session 跑选品流程，跑完自动结束。\n\n要我现在配吗？还是你想先测试一下今天能不能手动跑成功再定时？"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":506,"output":639,"cacheRead":115840,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":116985,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1779027898237,"responseId":"065902bf8cc09559e8ef28e1917c7ea5"}}
