{"type":"message","id":"a3ede42e","parentId":"c5cdc10e","timestamp":"2026-05-17T14:37:03.639Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The price is in \"$37536.00\" format - it seems like the \"$\" sign is followed by the price in VND (Vietnamese Dong), not USD. So $37536.00 means 37,536 VND, not $37,536 USD.\n\nSo the price filter of >= 50000 VND would give me products with price >= 50,000 VND (about $2 USD).\n\nBut looking at the filtered results, none of them actually have prices >= 50000 VND when I parse correctly:\n- Kẹp Tóc Lì Đơn Giản: $37536.00 = 37,536 VND (NOT >= 50000)\n\n\n- Băng Đô Dán Dính: $34780.00 = 34,780 VND (NOT >= 50000)\n- KẹP TóC KẹP TóC Đu ĐưA: $17000.00 = 17,000 VND (NOT >= 50000)\n\nAll of these fall below the 50,000 VND threshold, so I need to verify my parsing logic is actually catching the numeric values correctly.\n","thinkingSignature":"4d428e4191760ef965b03d0844a884552b9bf2f6379978da424d668ac79278c2"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_27bgxc9rhrfp_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"mcporter call sorftime-test.tiktok_category_report nodeId:908552 site:VN --output json 2>/dev/null | python3 -c \"\nimport json,sys,re\ndata = json.load(sys.stdin)\ntop50 = data.get('Top50产品', [])\ndef parse_price(p):\n    try:\n        # \\\"$37536.00\\\" -> 37536\n        return int(re.sub(r'[^\\d]', '', str(p)))\n    except:\n        return 0\n\nfiltered = [p for p in top50 if parse_price(p.get('价格',0)) >= 50000 and p.get('周销量环比',0) > 0]\nprint(f'>=50000VND 且增长>0: {len(filtered)} 个')\nfor p in filtered:\n    print(f\\\"月销:{p.get('月销量',0)} | 增长:{p.get('周销量环比',0)}% | 价:{p.get('价格','')} -> {parse_price(p.get('价格',0))}VND | {p.get('标题','')[:40]}\\\")\n\" 2>/dev/null"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":601,"output":507,"cacheRead":123264,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":124372,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUs